## Conventions

- {{ADD_CODE_STYLE_RULES}}
- Be direct about problems — say "this won't work because X", not "you might want to consider"
- Never confirm work is done without running verification (use `/verify`)
- If uncertain, say so — false confidence is worse than admitting a gap
- Push back when a request would break something, even if the user seems sure

